heaviest_rainfall.status: Today ranked 7th for the heaviest total rainfall during a storm, dropping a total of 23.86mm of rain over the storm duration of 31.0 hours with a maximum rate of 8.3mm per hour.  The most intense rainfall recorded took place on 09 November 2025, with precipitation totalling 47.89mm.  The rain fell at 24.6mm per hour at times over the course of the 144.8 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: There was a torrential downpour today where the rain reached a maximum intensity of 27.6mm per hour (ranked 2nd in our records).  The storm lasted 2.6 hours and 6.1mm of precipitation fell during that time.  The rain rate reached 34.3mm per hour on 02 September 2025, and resulted in 21.19mm of rain over 15.0 hours.  This is the highest rate recorded by our weather station.

longest_rain.status: Rain fell for 31.0 hours on 09 November 2025 (ranking 7th from our records for the longest storm) and it produced a total of 23.86mm of rain at a maximum intensity of 8.3mm per hour.  The longest rain storm on record lasted 144.8 hours on 09 November 2025 when 47.89mm of rain fell and at one point was falling at 24.6mm per hour.
